   754	    /// Cross-platform std.Io-backed server runtime.
   755	    ///
   756	    /// `std.Io.Threaded` is the first-party stdlib backend that currently
   757	    /// supports the Unix-domain socket control plane zmux uses on both macOS
   758	    /// and Linux, while fd readiness is handled by the platform poller
   759	    /// (`kqueue` on macOS, `epoll` on Linux, `poll` fallback elsewhere).
   760	    pub fn run(self: *Server) !void {
   761	        return self.runPoll();
